Package: Stat218Applet
Title: Statistical Inference Functions for Introductory Statistics course
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Asif", "Enan", , "aenan2@huskers.unl.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides functions for simulation-based and theory-based
    statistical inference, designed for use in STAT 218 at the University
    of Nebraska-Lincoln or any college level introductory statistics
    course. Terminology and methods follow the course textbook,
    Introduction to Statistical Investigations by Tintle, Chance, Cobb,
    Rossman, Roy, Swanson, and VanderStoep. The package offers a
    consistent workflow for hypothesis testing and confidence interval
    construction, each function produces a printed summary, a
    visualization of the null or sampling distribution, and a step-by-step
    walkthrough of the underlying mathematics.
